<subsection>    
    <title>Mathematical Writing Explorations</title>
            <exploration>
                <statement>An <m>n \times n</m> matrix <m>M</m> is <em>non-singular</em> if the associated homogeneous system with coefficient matrix <m>M</m> is consistent with one solution.
                    
<ul>
<li>Prove that the reduced row echelon form of <m>M</m> is the identity matrix.
</li>
<li>
Prove that, for any column vector <m>\vec{b} = (b_1,b_2,\ldots, b_n)</m>, the system of equations given by <m>\left[\begin{array}{c|c}M &amp; \vec{b}\end{array}
    \right]</m> has a unique solution.
</li>

<li>
    Prove that the columns of <m>M</m> form a basis for <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m>.</li>

<li>
    Prove that the rank of <m>M</m> is <m>n</m>.</li>
</ul>  
                </statement>
    </exploration>
